  <app loc="1">
   <rdg source="#MAC1949">Macalister (1949): FRATRES ORENT PRO NOBIS OGRECHU ET UGEN</rdg>
  </app>
 </listApp>      
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <p>May the brother's pray for us...</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary"> 
                <list type="witDetail">
                    <item n="1"><p>As pointed out by <ref source="#HAM2001">Hamlin (2001, 53)</ref>, <q>only the first four words are clear</q> in this inscription.</p></item>
                     <item n="2"><p>The word FRATRES indicates a community of some kind, and the subjunctive form ORENT suggests the translation `may the brothers pray for us' <ref source="#HAM2001">Hamlin 2001, 53-4</ref>).
                    </p></item></list>
            </div>
